 🎮 Video Game Sales Analysis

 Project Overview

This project analyzes the Video Game Sales dataset using Python to discover trends in the gaming industry through data cleaning, exploratory data analysis (EDA), visualization, and machine learning.
The objective was to identify which genres, platforms, publishers, and regions generated the highest sales and build a machine learning model to predict global video game sales.


 📂 Dataset

Dataset: Video Game Sales Dataset (vgsales.csv)

The dataset contains information about video games including:

 Name
 Platform
 Year
 Genre
 Publisher
 North America Sales
 Europe Sales
 Japan Sales
 Other Region Sales
 Global Sales

🛠 Technologies Used

 Python
 Pandas
 NumPy
 Matplotlib
 Scikit-learn
 Google Colab

 📊 Data Cleaning

The following preprocessing steps were performed:

 Removed missing values using `dropna()`
 Verified duplicate records
 Explored data types and summary statistics

 📈 Exploratory Data Analysis

The project includes:

 Global Sales by Genre
 Global Sales by Platform
 Top 10 Publishers
 Global Sales by Year
 Regional Sales Analysis
 Top 10 Best-Selling Games
 Distribution of Global Sales
 Boxplot for Outlier Detection
 Correlation Analysis

🔍 Key Findings

 Action games generated the highest global sales.
 PS2 was the highest-selling gaming platform.
 Nintendo achieved the highest
